wants
> to stay compatible with Windows/Linux/Mac servers.

The memprot envvar is needed if you wish to use the PPC's MMU.
The EnAlignExc envvar is needed to pass alignment errors
to the Mac. Both are VITAL to the emulation. What Sam needs
to do is make it where these things are not envvars that are
either OFF or ON, they need to be controlled on the fly by
the running programs.

- Joseph Fenton (taken from MSTech mailing-list)



