@node 08524.002
Subject: Re: How do I get the Shogo Demo working ?
From: Hans-Joerg Frieden <Hans-JoergF@hyperion-software.de>
Date: Fri, 4 May 2001 16:28:27 +0200

On Friday 04 May 2001 14:31, AB wrote:

> PowerPC Alignment exception

Installed iFusion lately ? :-)

This is actually easy to fix. You need to delete this variable:
     EnAlignExc

from ENVARC:PowerPC and set this variable
     memprot
to 0, then reboot.

iFusion installs these for reasons that are beyond me, since the EnAlignExc 
is only useful for developers for tuning programs, and will usually not make 
your system any better. Shogo needs unaligned access, though, since it wants 
to stay compatible with Windows/Linux/Mac servers.

memprot should always be set to 0 for Warp3D programs.

Best regards,
-- 
